column86: Cont1 Valve Or Device Fail Ind

column169: SHPX 211450 was found by an FRA inspector in the Belen, NM yard with multiple securement issues including an open vapor valve with a missing plug. The valve was secured and plug properly installed as well as securing the rest of the minor issues. No liquid release, just vapor. The car was released back into transportation.
column170: The shipper must ensure that the packages are properly prepared for transportation to prevent future releases of hazardous materials.(NAR:134)

column63: Improper Preparation for Transportation; Improper Preparation for Transportation
column169: Freight was not properly packed, not block and braced, spilled in transit.
column170: Retrain employees in proper loading procedures.
